BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Library of Congress] The Two Georges: Parallel Lives in an Age of
  Revolution
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260314
DTSTAMP:20260314T224131Z
UID:030e0de0-d898-47a5-8e10-bac3c007c301@dc-events-calendar
CATEGORIES:Cultural Centers,Library of Congress
DESCRIPTION:Our understanding of George Washington and King George III of 
 Britain is clouded by myths that have accumulated over centuries. This exh
 ibition explores the lives and legacies of the two adversaries during Amer
 ica’s war for independence. The Library of Congress brings their papers 
 together for the first time to reveal the real men behind the myths.\n\nSo
 urce: Library of Congress\n\nCategory: Cultural Centers\n\nLink: https://w
 ww.loc.gov/item/event-416122/the-two-georges-parallel-lives-in-an-age-of-r
 evolution/2026-03-14/
URL:https://www.loc.gov/item/event-416122/the-two-georges-parallel-lives-i
 n-an-age-of-revolution/2026-03-14/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[Library of Congress] Treasures from the Stephen Sondheim Collecti
 on
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260314
DTSTAMP:20260314T224131Z
UID:dfe9327b-70a3-452b-aff1-bbfccf3f5290@dc-events-calendar
CATEGORIES:Cultural Centers,Library of Congress
DESCRIPTION:In 2025\, the Library of Congress acquired the papers of Steph
 en Sondheim\, one of the most celebrated figures in twentieth-century musi
 cal theater. This small display in the Performing Arts Reading Room featur
 es highlights from the collection\, including lyrics and music from his mu
 sicals "Into the Woods\," "Sunday in the Park with George\," "Merrily We R
 oll Along\," "Sweeney Todd" and "A Little Night \n\nSource: Library of Con
 gress\n\nCategory: Cultural Centers\n\nLink: https://www.loc.gov/item/even
 t-419398/treasures-from-the-stephen-sondheim-collection/2026-03-14/
URL:https://www.loc.gov/item/event-419398/treasures-from-the-stephen-sondh
 eim-collection/2026-03-14/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
